@@TJvBitBtn.DropDownMenu
Summary
  Identifies a pop-up menu associated with the button.
Description
	Assign a value to DropDownMenu to make a menu appear when the button is pressed. (To display
  the menu programmatically, call the speed button’s Click method.) If the menu’s AutoPopup
  property is set to True, the menu appears automatically. If AutoPopup is False, display
  the menu by calling the menu’s Popup method in the speed button’s OnClick event handler.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvBitBtn.HintColor
Summary
  Determines the color of the Help Hint boxes of the button.
Description
  Use HintColor to specify the hint box color. Default this color has the value clInfoBk.
  To change the HintColor assign it a new TColor value.
See Also
  HotTrack
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvBitBtn.HotTrack
Summary
  Specifies whether the button is highlighted when the mouse passes over it.
Description
  Set HotTrack to True to provide visual feedback when the button is under the mouse. When HotTrack
  is False, there is no visual feedback when the mouse passes over the button.
See Also
  HotTrackFont, HotGlyph
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvBitBtn.HotTrackFont
Summary
  Specifies the font used when the mouse passes over the button, and HotTrack is True.
Description
  When the mouse passes over the button and HotTrack is set to True, HotTrackFont is used as the
  font for the button text.
	To change the font, change the value of the Charset, Color, Height, Name, Pitch, Size,
  and/or Style of the HotrackFont property.
See Also
  HotTrack
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvBitBtn.HotGlyph
Summary
  Specifies the bitmap that appears on the button when the mouse points to it.
Description
  Set HotGlyph to a bitmap object that contains the image that should appear on the face of the
  button when the mouse passes over it at runtime. If HotGlyph is unassigned, a TJvBitBtn
  button retains it's regular image (specified by the Glyph property) when the mouse passes
  over the button.
See Also
	HotTrack
